{"_id":"5a7dc694-8903-3e21-9b62-34fae0d2c741","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"There's no UI thread in web apps.\r\n\r\nAll network access is asynchronous by nature. The client can be synchronous or asynchronous, and the server can be synchronous or asynchronous - they both make the decision that is most natural for themselves, without regard to the other side. (Exception: Browser clients *must* be asynchronous).","postId":"2013_11_taskrun-etiquette-examples-dont-use-a63e8aa8-3250-37a4-990d-af802d3197e6","replyTo":"64c85f15-9192-31ce-b559-3b4779fa8b5a","date":"2016-11-27T23:57:54Z","timestamp":1480291074,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}